      "author": "doge-liang",
      "description": "Plugin-review fix release.\n\n- **No dynamic `<script>` injection in previews.** The bundled drawio viewer now runs via indirect eval in the page's global scope (identical semantics to a top-level script, no script element created), and drawio's sole external-script loader (an unused MathJax-from-CDN helper) is stripped at build time. This clears the two `createElement(\"script\")` findings — previews fetch and execute no external code.\n\nVerified in a real browser: the viewer loads, diagrams render to SVG at the correct size, and text labels (including CJK) are preserved.",
